eu.amidst.core.datastream.filereaders

Interface DataRow

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataRowMissing, DataRowWeka

    public interface DataRow
    This interface defines a row of the data matrix. It represents a specific assignment to all the attributes in the data.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Attributes getAttributes()
      Returns the set of Attributes that have observed values in this DataRow.
      double getValue(Attribute att)
      Returns the value assigned to a given Attribute in this DataRow.
      void setValue(Attribute att, double value)
      Sets the value of an Attribute in this DataRow.
      double[] toArray()
      Returns all the values of this DataRow as an array of doubles.

    • Method Detail

      • getValue

        double getValue(Attribute att)
        Returns the value assigned to a given Attribute in this DataRow.
        Parameters:
        att - an Attribute object.
        Returns:
        the assigned value to the given Attribute. If the attribute is not observed, then returns a Double.NaN value.

      • setValue

        void setValue(Attribute att,
              double value)
        Sets the value of an Attribute in this DataRow. If the value is already included in the data, then the value will be updated accordingly.
        Parameters:
        att - an Attribute object.
        value - a double value to be assigned to the given Attribute.

      • getAttributes

        Attributes getAttributes()
        Returns the set of Attributes that have observed values in this DataRow.
        Returns:
        a valid Attributes object.

      • toArray

        double[] toArray()
        Returns all the values of this DataRow as an array of doubles.
        Returns:
        an array of doubles.
